parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Ignition Switch and Passlock System Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch and Passlock system can cause the vehicle to stall or not start, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle will not start
the security light comes on
the vehicle stalls while driving
the key gets stuck in the ignition
the vehicle shuts off without warning
the doors lock and unlock randomly
and the hazard lights fail to work.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to stall or not start, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle's electrical system fails
causing the vehicle to stall or not start
the security light comes on
the vehicle's lights and accessories malfunction
and the vehicle's computer system fails.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel system can cause fuel leaks, fuel fumes to enter the vehicle, and engine stalling, which can lead to accidents, fires, or explosions, posing a significant risk to the driver and passengers.
symptoms: Strong odor of gasoline or fuel fumes inside the vehicle
fuel leaks
engine stalling
difficulty starting the engine
ticking noise from the flashers
dim or inoperative headlights
and faulty signal lights.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause faulty signal lights, dim or inoperative headlights, and faulty flashers, which can increase the risk of accidents, especially at night or in low-visibility conditions.
symptoms: Faulty signal lights
dim or inoperative headlights
faulty flashers
and ticking noise from the flashers.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine stalling can cause loss of control, accidents, and strand the driver and passengers, especially on highways or busy roads.
symptoms: Engine stalling
difficulty starting the engine
and faulty flashers.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the window regulators can cause inconvenience and discomfort to the driver and passengers, especially in hot or cold weather conditions.
symptoms: Inoperative window regulators
faulty window regulators.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the turn signals can cause confusion to other drivers, leading to potential accidents, and may also be a sign of a larger electrical issue that can cause smoke to emanate from the steering column, potentially leading to a fire.
symptoms: The turn signals do not shut off
click constantly
flicker
or do not work at all
the hazard lights do not work
smoke comes from the steering column
the airbag warning light is on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the multifunction switch can cause the turn signals to malfunction, leading to potential accidents, and may also cause smoke to emanate from the steering column, potentially leading to a fire.
symptoms: The turn signals do not shut off
click constantly
flicker
or do not work at all
smoke comes from the steering column
the airbag warning light is on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the brake lights can cause other drivers to not be aware of the vehicle's intentions, leading to potential accidents.
symptoms: The brake lights do not work
people have told the driver that the brake lights are out
but when taken to the dealership
they are told they are working properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can cause serious injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The airbag did not deploy in an accident
the airbag warning light is on.
